						<summary>

						<p>On the wall of the Īśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Rāmachandra, 1289 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated the cyclic year Virōdhi, Kārttika ba. 30, Monday, the regnal year of the king being lost. The details, however, correspond, to 1289 A.D., November 14.</p>						

						<p>It seems to record a gift of land to the goddess installed by a lady. The details of the transaction are not clear. The inscription is damaged.</p>						

						</summary>
